# 📘 **SOP – Kafka Console (Streamshub) Implementation & Troubleshooting**

---

## ✅ **VERSION 1: Confluence-Ready SOP**

---

## **1. Purpose**

This document defines the standard procedure for:

* Deploying Kafka Console (Streamshub) on OpenShift
* Integrating Kafka metrics with OpenShift Monitoring (Prometheus/Thanos)
* Troubleshooting Kafka Console metrics issues

---

## **2. Scope**

Applicable to:

* Dev, SIT, UAT, Pre-Prod, and Production environments
* Strimzi Kafka clusters deployed on OpenShift
* Teams: DevOps, Platform Engineering, Kafka Admins

---

## **3. Architecture Overview**

Kafka Console depends on the following components:

| Component                             | Description                 |
| ------------------------------------- | --------------------------- |
| Kafka Cluster (Strimzi)               | Source of Kafka data        |
| JMX Prometheus Exporter               | Exposes Kafka metrics       |
| PodMonitor                            | Enables Prometheus scraping |
| OpenShift Monitoring (Thanos Querier) | Metrics backend             |
| Kafka Console                         | UI for visualization        |

**Important:**
Kafka Console retrieves metrics from Prometheus, not directly from Kafka.

---

